Sentencas: A series of perovskite oxides SrBiMTiO6 (M = Fe, Mn, Cr) have been synthesized and characterized towards application as cathode materials for solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs).
Titulo: Electrical and electrochemical properties of SrBiMTiO6 (M = Fe, Mn, Cr) as potential cathodes for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: X-ray diffraction (XRD) patterns reveal that all samples are stabilized in space group.
Titulo: Electrical and electrochemical properties of SrBiMTiO6 (M = Fe, Mn, Cr) as potential cathodes for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Electrical conductivity, AC impedance characteristics, and thermal and chemical stability have been studied in order to assess their possible use as SOFC cathode materials.
Titulo: Electrical and electrochemical properties of SrBiMTiO6 (M = Fe, Mn, Cr) as potential cathodes for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: In comparison with other low electrical conductivity cathodes of SOFC, our results suggest that SrBiMnTiO6, which has the highest electrical conductivity (4.02 S cm(-1)) and moderate polarization resistance (0.104 Omega cm(2)) at 850 A degrees C, is the most promising candidate among the three perovskite oxides for further study and optimization as a SOFC cathode material.
Titulo: Electrical and electrochemical properties of SrBiMTiO6 (M = Fe, Mn, Cr) as potential cathodes for solid oxide fuel cells
